7:
Though we continue to endure trials
in this distant land of Palpebra, I am
deeply thankful to welcome the new
year with you all.
10:
O Stars, light up the path of the
faithful with your radiant glory.
14:
We ask that you bless all your
children, no matter where they be.
Now come, let us say a prayer
together.
21:
...And then I was stuck doing New
Year's prayers for the entire day!
25:
The year just started and I'm already
DONE with it!
29:
We stopped by during a public
prayer, and yeah... It was quite the
marathon session.
32:
But, uh... Are you sure the church is
okay with you wearing that?
36:
This getup was a gift from the
merchant's guild. They're very
business-oriented, so if they can
make a profit off of cultures from
other worlds, they will.
40:
Besides, it's not like any of the other
priests are going to know the origin
or purpose of this outfit. It's fine!
52:
A-anyway! I finally managed to find
some time so I stopped by to take a
breather.
60:
Yep. We're headed to a shrine in
Yamato.
70:
You sure you're up for it? It's quite
the hike.
75:
Piece of cake! I've been taking lots of
breaks and going on walks recently,
and now I'm fit as a fiddle!
78:
I'm not gonna get winded like last
time, don't you worry.
96: I said I'd carry you, didn't I?
100:
I'm not good with motion sickness,
okay
108:
Heh. A pickpocket, eh? Guess that's
what happens when you try to rob a
saint.
113:
...The Stars' protection reaches me
even on another world...
116:
W-wait a second! I've heard about
this! They say a celestial maiden
visited a certain village... And she
called down a mystical light from
the heavens!
118:
Our Lady! Mistress of the Heavens!
We are in awe of your divine
presence!
121: H-huh?! Wh-what should I do now?!
130:
Well... It's good to know I'm welcome
here, I guess...
134:
This was bound to happen with an
outfit like that. Are you sure it's okay
for you to stay here?
139:
...As long as nobody finds out what I
actually am!
145:
Had we stayed any longer, the
crowd would have only grown.
150:
Please forgive the intrusion, Mistress!
I have something I must ask you!
159:
Compared to the Heavenly Mistress,
my power is nothing. But visitors to
the shrine still depend on it...
161:
But, with my powers... I'm far too
weak to save everyone from their
troubles!
163: Mistress! I beg you, please help
166:
Huh?
...Take it easy on yourself. Nobody
can save everyone from everything!
170:
And neither can I! Even as a saint,
I'm always looking for a chance to
dodge duties and take it easy!
178:
Nobody can just... Shoulder the
burdens of the whole world.
182:
I... see...
Then, even with your power...
185:
But you don't want to stop trying to
help others, do you?
189:
Your prayer to save those in need is
a noble one, so let's just focus on
what we can do rather than our
limitations.
193:
Oh, but if you start feeling tired or
down on yourself, you gotta take it
easy! Even if that means stopping
everything for a marathon
snoozefest!
200:
That's right! You're always helping
others with your prayers, but you
gotta loosen up sometimes and be
kind to yourself, too!
203:
How about letting this slacker saint
help you out a little?
209:
You've got a festival coming up,
don't you? I'll lend you a hand, if
you'd like!
227:
Nobody said anything about
dancing! Being able to rain down
divine punishment is one thing... But
dancing?
240:
I gotta calm down! Okay, uh... Take a
step, spin... Like this?
